  "texts": [
    "It is easy to see that this frame validates exactly the same formulas as the Kripke frame ⟨N, <⟩.",
    "Indeed, any possibility frame, like this one, in which every state is refined by an endpoint (world, instant) is semantically equivalent to a Kripke frame based on those endpoints (see § 4.2).",
    "Yet this frame is a good example of how assumptions about relations and modal axioms from Kripke semantics must be reconsidered in possibility semantics.",
    "For example, our R < is functional, and yet ♢ < p → □ < p is not valid.",
    "(Later we will see that for any full possibility frame, there is a semantically equivalent one in which the relations are partially functional.)"
  ],
